The Wedge is a 30 minute weekly music program airing on Canadian music TV station MuchMusic.


Since 2011, the show is hosted by Damian Abraham, lead singer of the band Fucked Up.


The Wedge primarily focuses on music videos, but will periodically have live performances, interviews, and panel discussions.


The Wedge is by and large associated with alternative music, although it often hosts music from other genres as well. Mostly independent releases.
